Get cluster info

aws eks describe-nodegroup \
--cluster-name <your-cluster> \
--nodegroup-name <nodegroup-name> \
--query "nodegroup.nodeRole"

You will get something like:
arn:aws:iam::123456789:role/eks-node-role

Attach Required Policy

Attach this policy to the node role:
aws iam attach-role-policy \
--role-name <node-role> \
--policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/service-role/AmazonEBSCSIDriverPolicy

ADDON
eksctl create addon   --name aws-ebs-csi-driver   --cluster my-eks-cluster-1503   --region us-east-1


storage-class.yaml

apiVersion: storage.k8s.io/v1
kind: StorageClass
metadata:
  name: ebs-sc
provisioner: ebs.csi.aws.com
volumeBindingMode: WaitForFirstConsumer
parameters:
  type: gp3
reclaimPolicy: Delete or Retain

storage-class-pvc.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: ebs-pvc
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  storageClassName: ebs-sc
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 5Gi

deployment.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx
        volumeMounts:
        - mountPath: "/data"
          name: my-storage
      volumes:
      - name: my-storage
        persistentVolumeClaim:
          claimName: my-pvc

Architecture Flow or Complete Flow (Very Important)
Deployment → Pod → PersistentVolumeClaim → StorageClass → AWS EBS CSI Driver → AWS EBS Volume → Attached to EKS Worker Node

Real Example in EKS (When PVC is created)
PVC → StorageClass → creates EBS automatically
